race.comment: CROSSOVERKID (3) resumes over a very suitable trip. He was narrowly beaten fresh last time over 1300m and was good in two runs thereafter when getting over more ground. This trip looks ideal and he has the class to take this out. GIRLS NIGHT (5) steps up to a mile for the first time having stuck on gamely at Sandown Lakeside last time out to finish third. She is a winner over 1550m and maps for every chance. THE DAILY PLANET (7) broke through for his second career win when last seen at Terang, finishing strongly to get up by 0.8 lengths. He draws well again and could measure up. SHREWSBURY ROAD (6) ran well fresh over 1400m and will only improve as he gets over more ground. PALACE WINTER (11) is back off a short break but has minor claims.
